    "body": "This would be nonstraightforward: without knowing any LLVM specifics, I'd guess it uses a C assert implementation, which raises SIGABRT. Encapsulating every single call to libllvm that rustc makes would be a huge perf problem, so I expect the best way would be to hack LLVM itself.\n",
